%20summary%20examples-1.jpeg" title="" width="650" height="357" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; 显示：块；宽度：650px；高度：auto ; max-width: 100%;">;</h3>; <p>;活动行业委员会的执行摘要简短而精彩，但为读者提供了大量信息，以了解该组织的业务及其提供的产品。请注意使命、愿景和价值观部分的简洁性，这表明如果不适合您，则无需详细说明。 “我们是谁”部分在这里最为强调，这是吸引读者注意力的有力技巧。</p>; <h4>;亲自尝试</h4>; <p>;在您感觉的部分花费更多时间你的听众最关心的。如果您要向投资者推销，您可能会在市场分析和财务部分花费更多时间。如果您的写作对象是普通读者，您可能会关注您的公司背景。</p>; <h3>;3. <a href="https://www.companyshopgroup.co.uk/about-us">;公司商店组</a>;</h3>; <h3>;<img alt="执行摘要示例：公司商店组" src ="https://blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Google%20Drive%20Integration/DRAFT%20executive%20summary%20examples-2.jpeg?width=650&amp;height=347&amp;name=DRAFT%20executive% 20summary%20examples-2.jpeg" title="" width="650" height="347" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max -width: 100%;">;</h3>; <p>;访问 Company Shop Group 的“关于我们”页面时，首先看到的内容之一是其副标题：“Company Shop Group 是英国领先的剩余食品和家居产品再分销商。 ”与 Connected 一样，Company Shop Group 也将其业务放在首位，以便读者可以选择继续阅读或离开以了解该公司的业务。该组织还包括多媒体来吸引访问者并以更易于理解的格式解释其业务模式。</p>; <h4>;亲自尝试</h4>; <p>;包括您在首屏上所做的事情并添加多媒体元素以提供让读者更多地了解您的另一种方式。视频、图像和标题可以让您更轻松地浏览执行摘要，但请注意仅针对正确的受众并通过正确的媒体使用此方法。 （例如，您可能不会在正式的商业计划中包含图像。）</p>; <h3>;4。 <a href="https://www.firstenergycorp.com/about.html">;FirstEnergy</a>;</h3>; <h3>;<img alt="执行摘要示例：第一能源" src="https:// /blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Google%20Drive%20Integration/DRAFT%20executive%20summary%20examples.jpeg?width=650&amp;height=582&amp;name=DRAFT%20executive%20summary%20examples.jpeg”标题="" width="650" height="582" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;">;< /h3>; <p>;如果您是一个更加企业化、正式的品牌，FirstEnergy 的执行摘要将为您提供很大的启发。公司的执行摘要涵盖其使命、子公司、运营、产品和服务、企业责任价值观和战略计划目标。由于该公司是公开交易的，这对潜在投资者来说是有用的信息。</p>; <p>;虽然内容很全面，但执行摘要仍然很简短，使用要点和图像来分解信息，让读者有机会探索更多内容带有侧边栏菜单。</p>; <h4>;亲自尝试</h4>; <p>;在撰写执行摘要时，请注意您公司的状况。如果是公开交易，您将需要包含更多信息，例如您的战略计划和扩张机会。如果您要在网站上发布执行摘要，请使用侧边栏让读者无需离开自己的位置即可从一页跳转到另一页。</p>; <h2>;开始您的执行摘要</h2>; <p>;执行摘要应简短明了，但仍应传达您作为一家公司的身份。如果您要创办一家公司，请记住讲述您的故事，同时还包括重要的背景和财务信息。强有力的执行摘要将为更多投资者投资您的业务以及更多客户信任您的品牌铺平道路。</p>; <p>;<em>;编者注：本文最初于 2018 年 12 月发布，现已更新为了全面性。</em>;</p>; <p>;<em>;本文是由人类撰写的，但我们的团队在编辑过程中使用了人工智能。查看</em>;<em>;<a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/how-the-hubspot-blog-team-uses-ai">;我们的完整披露</a>;</ em>;<em>;了解有关我们如何使用人工智能的更多信息。</em>;</p>; <p>;<em>;<a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ ci/?pg=4511101c-c340-43b3-bbc9-99176aeb37f4&amp;pid=53&amp;ecid=&hseid=&amp;hsic=">;<img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !重要; 宽度: 自动 !重要; 最大宽度: 100% !重要;边框宽度: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; 边距: 0 自动; 显示: 块; 上边距: 20px; 下边距: 20px" alt="执行摘要提示" height="226" width="646" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/4511101c-c340-43b3-bbc9-99176aeb37f4 .png"align="middle">;</a>;</em>;</p>; <img src="https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=53&amp;k=14&amp;r= https%3A%2F%2Fblog.hubspot.com%2Fmarketing%2Fexecutive-summary-examples&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.hubspot.com%252Fmarketing&amp;bvt=rss" alt="" width="1" height ="1" style="min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0 !重要;左边距:0!重要;顶部填充:0!重要;底部填充:0!重要;右填充:0!重要;左填充:0!重要; ” >;商业工具Thu, 31 Aug 2023 11:00:00 GMT https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/executive-summary-examples 2023-08-31T11:00:00Z卡罗琳·福西
如何撰写出色的电子邮件签名 [+专业示例] https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/professional-email-signatures <div class="hs-featured-image-wrapper">; <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/professional-email-signatures" title="" class="hs-featured-image-链接">; <img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hubfs/69_%20How%20to%20Write%20a%20Press%20Release%20%5BFree%20Press%20Release%20Template%20+%20Examples%5D .png" alt="用手和打字机的专业电子邮件签名示例" class="hs-featured-image" style="width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0 ;">; </a>; </div>; <p>;在全球范围内，超过 <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/456500/daily-number-of-e-mails-worldwide /">;平均每天发送和接收 300 封电子邮件</a>;。这是在您发送的个人电子邮件中推销您自己和您的业务的 300 个机会。 </p>; <p>;在全球范围内，每天发送和接收超过 <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/456500/daily-number-of-e-mails-worldwide/">;300 多封电子邮件平均而言。这是在您发送的个人电子邮件中推销您自己和您的业务的 300 个机会。 </p>; <p>;很多人都把他们的电子邮件签名视为事后的想法，这是一个很大的错失机会。这些签名让您有机会清楚地表明自己是谁，让人们可以轻松地联系到您，并为人们提供一个了解更多信息的地方——无论是关于您、您的业务还是您所从事的事情。正在处理。</p>; <a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=3a319a89-ebd2-48ad-94d8-a7b3cc5aa634&amp;pid=53&amp;ecid= &amp;hseid=&amp;hsic=">;<img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px ; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="只需点击几下即可创建新的品牌电子邮件签名。从这里开始。（免费。）" height="60" width="775" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/3a319a89-ebd2-48ad-94d8-a7b3cc5aa634 .png"align="middle">;</a>; <p>;因此，如果您只是在签名中输入您的姓名和一两点联系信息，那么您就没有充分利用连接的机会并与您发送电子邮件的人互动。那么您的签名中到底应该包含哪些内容？</p>; <br>; <h3>;1.名字和姓氏</h3>; <p>;就像普通邮件通信一样，应始终包含您的姓名，以便邮件的收件人知道邮件来自谁。这体现在电子邮件签名中，通常是第一行文本。</p>; <h3>;2.隶属信息（例如职务和部门）</h3>; <p>;紧跟在您的姓名后面的应该是您的隶属信息。您的隶属关系可能包括您的职位、您的公司或组织、和/或什至您的部门。当然，当您与收件人建立关系时，您的名字最终应该成为自己的吸引力，但提供此信息可以提供有关对话以及您在其中的角色的更多背景信息。</p>; <p>;此外，将自己与收件人联系起来较大的组织会给您带来更高的可信度，特别是如果它是一个知名的组织。这可以帮助您吸引读者的注意力，以便他们认真对待您的信息。</p>; <h3>;3.次要联系信息</h3>; <p>;次要联系信息也很重要，以便收件人知道如何与您联系。次要信息可能包括电话、传真或您想要强调的任何其他通信方式。在您不想放弃直线电话的情况下，您可以利用这个机会宣传您的个人网站 - 这是一种打开沟通渠道的被动方式，如果您不想要的话，也不会淹没自己的外展活动。</ p>; <h3>;4。社交资料图标</h3>; <p>;您的社交媒体存在是<a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/sales/the-ultimate-guide-to-personal-branding?__hstc= 45788219.7a8e373dcdf4afab74c1ec6781de1784.1650465797294.1650465797294.1650465797294.1&__hssc=45788219.1.1650465797296&__hsfp= 4140801928&_ga=2.172349350.481601421.1650465796-20625558.1650465796">;您的个人品牌</a>;，因为它可以帮助您在自己的空间中获得关注者并向人们展示您所关心的内容关于。您可以通过一个人发布的内容以及他们的自我形象来了解他们的很多信息。</p>; <p>;这就是为什么在电子邮件签名中包含社交媒体页面的链接是个好主意。它不仅可以强化您的个人品牌，还可以帮助人们找到联系和关注您的新方式。</p>; <p>;更好吗？如果您在社交媒体上发布指向该内容的链接，它可以帮助增加您的在线内容的流量。因此，如果您确实在签名中包含社交图标，请确保您的社交个人资料保持最新状态，并充满有趣的相关内容。 （换句话说，如果您六个月没有发推文，您可能希望将 Twitter 排除在外。）</p>; <p>;为什么使用社交媒体图标而不是简单的文本链接？因为图标对于浏览您签名的人来说更容易识别 - 并且它们会从其中的其余文本中脱颖而出。根据 <a href="https://neomam.com/interactive/13reasons/">;NeoMam Studios</a>; 的研究，以彩色显示的视觉效果可以使人们阅读其余内容的意愿提高 80%。这是一个巨大的优势。另外，在您可能要存放大量信息的地方，图标可以节省大量空间。</p>; <p>;即使您出现在许多社交媒体网站上，也要尽量限制图标的数量。图标增加到五个或六个。专注于对发展您的业务或建立个人品牌最重要的帐户。</p>; <p>;如果您确实包含大量社交媒体图标，请至少尝试减少其他内容（如果可能），以便您的设计不太忙。查看下面的示例，使用 <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/email-signature-generator?hubs_post=blog.hubspot.com/marketing/professional-email-signatures&amp;hubs_post-cta=HubSpot 制作%27s%20Email%20Signature%20Generator&amp;__hstc=45788219.7a8e373dcdf4afab74c1ec6781de1784.1650465797294.1650465797294.1650465797294.1&amp;__hssc=457882 19.1.1650465797296&amp;__hsfp=4140801928&amp;_ga=2.172349350.481601421.1650465796-20625558.1650465796">;HubSpot 的电子邮件签名生成器</a>;。</p >; <p>;<img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/professional-email-signatures_0.webp?width=400&amp;height=276&amp;name=professional-email-signatures_0.webp " alt="电子邮件签名中包含的内容：社交个人资料图标" width="400" height="276" style="height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 400px;">;</p>; <h3>;5。号召性用语</h3>; <p>;在电子邮件签名中可以做的最明智的事情之一就是包含号召性用语。最好的电子邮件签名 CTA 是简单的、最新的、不咄咄逼人的，并且符合您的电子邮件风格，使它们看起来更像是后记，而不是推销。</p>; <p>;选择与您当前的业务目标之一相一致的 CTA，并在这些目标发生变化时进行更新。以下是 HubSpotter 电子邮件签名的示例，其中包含 <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/podcastnetwork">;HubSpot Podcast Network</a>; 的 CTA：</p>; <p>;<a href ="https://www.hubspot.com/podcastnetwork">;<img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/professional-email-signatures_3.webp?width=400&amp;height= 248&name=professional-email-signatures_3.webp" alt="专业电子邮件签名中的 HubSpot 播客网络 CTA" width="400" height="248" style="height: auto; max-width: 100%; width : 400px;">;</a>;</p>; <h3>;6.预订链接</h3>; <p>;如果您发现自己与想要与您预订会议的同事和客户来回发送电子邮件，请在您的电子邮件签名中添加一个预订日历的链接，让他们更轻松。下面是我们自己的 <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bryanlowry1/">;Bryan Lowry</a>; 的示例。</p>; <p>;有很多工具可以会帮助人们预约。如果您是 HubSpot Sales 客户，您可以<a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/sales/schedule-meeting?hubs_post=blog.hubspot.com/marketing/professional-email-signatures&amp; hubs_post-cta=share%20your%20personalized%20meeting%20link&amp;__hstc=45788219.7a8e373dcdf4afab74c1ec6781de1784.1650465797294.1650465797294.1650465797294.1&amp;__h ssc=45788219.1.1650465797296&__hsfp=4140801928&amp;_ga=2.172349350.481601421.1650465796-20625558.1650465796">;分享您的个性化会议链接</ a>; 与您想要预约会面的任何人联系，让他们从您的空闲时间中进行选择。如果您愿意，您可以让 HubSpot CRM 自动为预订会议的任何人创建新的联系人记录（如果尚不存在）。</p>; <p>;<a href="https://www. hubspot.com/email-signature-generator">;<img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Google%20Drive%20Integration/professional-email-signature-example-vertical-hubspot. png?width=500&amp;height=529&amp;name=professional-email-signature-example-vertical-hubspot.png" alt="专业电子邮件签名示例：hubspot 垂直布局" width="500" height="529" 样式="height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 500px;">;</a>;</p>; <p>;如果您不是 HubSpot 客户，一个很棒的会议工具是 <a href="https ://calendly.com/">;Calendly</a>;，基本版免费，可让您集成 Google 或 Office 365 日历。 If you're looking for a <a href="https://www.growthmarketingpro.com/the-5-best-calendly-alternatives-for-productivity-in-2020/">;Calendly alternative</a>;, <a href="https://youcanbook.me/pricing/">;YouCanBook.me</a>; is another booking tool that goes for $7 per calendar per month.</p>; <h3>;7. Industry Disclaimer or Legal Requirements</h3>; <p>;Some industries such as legal, financial, and insurance have specific guidelines on email usage and etiquette to protect private information from being transmitted. For this reason, you may want to look into what regulations your industry has in place and include a disclaimer in your signature about email transmissions. Mail-Signatures offers a number of email disclaimer examples, including this one:</p>; <p>;<em>;"The content of this email is confidential and intended for the recipient specified in the message only. It is strictly forbidden to share any part of this message with any third party, without a written consent of the sender. If you received this message by mistake, please reply to this message and follow with its deletion, so that we can ensure such a mistake does not occur in the future."</em>;</p>; <h3>;8. Photo or Logo</h3>; <p>;An image is a great choice to spice up your email signature. If you want a personal touch so that recipients you've never met can associate your name with your face, consider using a professional photo in your signature. Alternatively, you can use the company's logo to add more brand awareness to the email.</p>; <h3>;9. Pronouns</h3>; <p>;While not as common in email signatures and certainly not required, adding your preferred pronouns to your signature is helpful, especially when emailing individuals you've never met. It also takes ambiguity away if you have a name perceived as gender-neutral.</p>; <p>;Now that you know the elements you should include, what does a great email signature look like? Here are some tips for creating signatures that are helpful and professional, including a few great examples.</p>; <p>;</p>; <h3>;1. Emphasize your name, affiliation, and secondary contact information.</h3>; <p>;As you might guess, your name comes first. Closely following your name, however, should be your affiliation and where else people can reach you.</p>; <p>;Your affiliation could mean your job title, your company, your school, or a similar organization that you deem important to your recipients. Your name should eventually be its own draw, of course, but using a more popular brand name — and even its logo — ensures you get the attention of your readers and they take your message seriously.</p>; <p>;Secondary contact information is important, too. You might not want to endorse your personal phone number, but you could take this opportunity to promote your personal website — a passive way to open the lines of communication without flooding yourself with outreach you don't want.</p>; <p>;Here's a <a href="https://newoldstamp.com/email-signature-examples/">;sample email signature</a>; that hits on all three things described above nicely. Kevin's first and last name are accompanied by his affiliation with the University of Connecticut. He also promotes his personal website so his recipients have another outlet to see his work and contact him for more information.</p>; <p>;Want to create a signature like the one below? Use <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/email-signature-generator?hubs_post=blog.hubspot.com/marketing/professional-email-signatures&amp;hubs_post-cta=HubSpot%27s%20Email%20Signature%20Generator&amp;__hstc=45788219.7a8e373dcdf4afab74c1ec6781de1784.1650465797294.1650465797294.1650465797294.1&amp;__hssc=45788219.1.1650465797296&amp;__hsfp=4140801928&amp;_ga=2.172349350.481601421.1650465796-20625558.1650465796">;HubSpot's Email Signature Generator</a>;.</p>; <p>;<img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/professional-email-signatures_5.webp?width=458&amp;height=268&amp;name=professional-email-signatures_5.webp" alt="email signature for Kevin McLievie of University of Connecticut generated with HubSpot's Email Signature Generator" width="458" height="268" style="height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 458px;">;</p>; <h3>;2. Keep the colors simple and consistent.</h3>; <p>;Branding is most effective when it's consistent — and that includes your email signature. Adding color to your email signature is a nice touch that'll help it stand out from the rest of your email. But if you do choose to use color, be sure to stick to one or two in addition to dark text.</p>; <p>;Use subtle highlights to match your logo or branding, like <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/brittanyhodak">;Brittany Hodak</a>; does in her email signature, below. Notice how her social media icons are the same blue hue as the <a href="http://zinepak.com/">;ZinePak</a>; logo.</p>; <p>;<img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hs-fs/hubfs/professional-email-signatures_6.webp?width=313&amp;height=234&amp;name=professional-email-signatures_6.webp" alt="Professional email signature example by Brittany Hodak with multiple colors" width="313" height="234" style="width: 313px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;">;</p>; <h3>;3. Use design hierarchy.</h3>; <p>;Good design is all about presenting your information in an easily digestible manner. Because your email signature is likely more a list of information than it is a compelling story, you'll want to use hierarchy to direct readers' eyes to what they should be reading first.</p>; <p>;Scale your name up to a larger font so that it attracts the most attention, <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/resume-format-tips?__hstc=45788219.7a8e373dcdf4afab74c1ec6781de1784.1650465797294.1650465797294.1650465797294.1&amp;__hssc=45788219.1.1650465797296&amp;__hsfp=4140801928&amp;_ga=2.162337721.481601421.1650465796-20625558.1650465796">;like you would on a resume</a>;. Then, pick and choose information to bold and color based on importance so you can help guide people's eyes logically through the design.</p>; <h3>;4. Make links trackable.</h3>; <p>;So you put a few links in your email signature, including your CTA and your social media icons. But is anyone actually clicking on them?</p>; <p>;To figure out whether the links in your signature are actually attracting clicks and making an impact, you'll want to make those links trackable 